he%20Jaffrelot%2C%202024.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trajectory%20of%20this%20book%20has%20been%20atypical.%20I%20submitted%20the%20manuscript%20in%20late%202013%20in%20order%20to%20have%20it%20published%20before%20the%202014%20Indian%20elections.%20For%20publishers%2C%20election%20campaigns%20are%20usually%20a%20good%20time%20for%20selling%20political%20books.%20However%2C%20their%20legal%20advisors%20considered%20that%20this%20manuscript%20was%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20risk%E2%80%9D.The%20letter%20I%20received%2C%20summarising%20the%20legal%20assessments%2C%20claimed%20that%20some%20passages%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20deemed%20as%20hurtful%20towards%20the%20people%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20containing%20an%20unyielding%20view%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%E2%80%9D.%20While%20the%20manuscript%20had%20been%20carefully%20copy-edited%2C%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20cut%20so%20many%20passages%20that%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20my%20publisher%2C%20Michael%20Dwyer%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20let%20this%20book%20die%20because%20it%20was%20our%20duty%20to%20testify%20and%20present%20facts%20which%20were%20gradually%20fading%20away%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20censorship%20and%20self-censorship%20%E2%80%93%20regarding%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20the%20specific%20political%20modus%20operandi%20he%20invented%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20has%20always%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20apolitical%20CM%E2%80%9D.%20This%20claim%20extends%20back%20to%20his%20first%20faltering%20steps%20in%20the%20public%20arena%2C%20which%2C%20undeniably%2C%20have%20endowed%20him%20with%20a%20unique%20pedigree.%20But%20this%20claim%20needs%20to%20be%20scrutinised%20because%20it%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20had%20no%20ideology%3B%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20it%20reflected%20his%20sense%20of%20doctrinal%20purity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Damodardas%20Modi%20was%20born%20on%2017%20September%201950%20in%20the%20small%20town%20of%20Vadnagar%20(Mehsana%20district).%20He%20hails%20from%20the%20low%20caste%20of%20Modh%20Ghanchis%20(oil%20pressers)%2C%20which%20was%20added%20to%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Socially%20and%20Economically%20Backward%20Classes%20list%20in%201994%20and%20to%20the%20central%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBC)%20list%20in%201999.%20His%20father%20sold%20edible%20oil%2C%20but%20also%20had%20a%20tea%20stall%20where%20Narendra%2C%20according%20to%20most%20of%20his%20biographies%2C%20used%20to%20work%20as%20a%20child.%20He%20joined%20the%20local%20RSS%20shakha%20when%20he%20was%20seven%20or%20eight%20years%20old%20%E2%80%9Cbecause%20this%20was%20the%20only%20extra-curricular%20activity%20open%20for%20him%20outside%20his%20peer%20group%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20biography%20of%20Modi%20by%20M.V.%20Kamath%20and%20K.%20Randeri%2C%20he%20very%20early%20on%20showed%20%E2%80%9Can%20inclination%20towards%20becoming%20a%20sanyasi%20%5Bworld%20renouncer%5D%E2%80%9D.%20Such%20a%20calling%20is%20not%20uncommon%20in%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS).%20M.S.%20Golwalkar%20himself%20renounced%20the%20world%20before%20becoming%20number%20two%20in%20the%20organisation.%20Like%20him%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20went%20to%20the%20Belur%20Math%2C%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Ramakrishna%20Mission%20in%20Calcutta%20(today%E2%80%99s%20Kolkata)%2C%20and%20then%20to%20the%20Himalayas.%20In%20an%20interview%20he%20gave%20to%20Nilanjan%20Mukhopadhyay%20he%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20went%20to%20the%20Vivekananda%20Ashram%20in%20Almora%2C%20I%20loitered%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20Himalayas.%20I%20had%20some%20influences%20of%20spiritualism%20at%20that%20time%20along%20with%20the%20sentiment%20of%20patriotism%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20all%20mixed.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20delineate%20the%20two%20ideas.%E2%80%9D%20This%20collapsing%20of%20religion%20and%20a%20certain%20political%20culture%20is%20typical%20of%20Hindu%20nationalists%20who%2C%20since%20Savarkar%2C%20look%20at%20India%20as%20their%20punya%20bhoomi%20(sacred%20land)%20and%20matri%20bhoomi%20(mother%20land).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20326px)%2085vw%2C%20326px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22326%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web.jpeg%20391w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web-192x300.jpeg%20192w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696449%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22510%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChristophe%20Jaffrelot%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EGujarat%20Under%20Modi%3A%20Laboratory%20of%20Today%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHurst%20Publishers%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20biographer%20of%20Modi%2C%20Kingshuk%20Nag%2C%20does%20not%20mention%20this%20episode%20at%20all%20but%20highlights%20the%20fact%20that%20Modi%20left%20Vadnagar%20in%201967%2C%20when%20he%20was%2017%20years%20old%2C%20to%20escape%20a%20child%20marriage%20that%20had%20been%20arranged%20years%20before.%20In%20this%20version%2C%20Modi%20went%20to%20his%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20Ahmedabad%20(about%20110%20km%20away)%20directly%20from%20his%20home%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20became%20a%20full-time%20RSS%20worker%20by%20the%20late%201960s%20or%20early%201970s.%20He%20then%20started%20living%20at%20Hedgewar%20Bhawan%20(RSS%20headquarters)%20in%20the%20residential%20area%20of%20Maninagar%20(Ahmedabad)%20and%20became%20the%20assistant%20to%20the%20prant%20pracharak%20in%20charge%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20Lakshmanrao%20Inamdar%2C%20a%20former%20lawyer%20who%20regarded%20him%20as%20his%20manas%20putra%20(a%20son%20born%20out%20of%20the%20mind)%20and%20whom%20he%20regarded%20as%20his%20mentor.%20It%20seems%20that%20Modi%20became%20a%20pracharak%20as%20early%20as%201972.%20The%20next%20year%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20Navnirman%20agitation%2C%20after%20being%20dispatched%20by%20the%20RSS%20to%20the%20ABVP%2C%20the%20Indian%20Student%20Association%2C%20then%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20this%20movement.%20Around%20that%20time%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20Modi%20registered%20as%20an%20MA%20student%20at%20Gujarat%20University%20after%20passing%20his%20BA%20as%20an%20external%20student%20of%20Delhi%20University.%20In%201974%20or%201975%2C%20he%20became%20close%20to%20one%20of%20his%20professors%2C%20Pravin%20Sheth%2C%20who%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20an%20external%20student%20of%20post-graduate%20programme%20in%20Political%20Science%20at%20Gujarat%20University%2C%20Modi%20used%20to%20come%20to%20me%2C%20collect%20reading%20material%20from%20me%2C%20grasp%20the%20matter.%20He%20applied%20them%20in%20examinations%20and%20achieved%20first%20class%20first.%20After%20acquiring%20good%20understanding%20of%20Political%20Sociology%20and%20Indian%20Politics%2C%20with%20his%20unique%20sense%2C%20he%20had%20applied%20the%20theory%20of%20Political%20Science%20in%20practice%20with%20appropriate%20adaptations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20was%20then%20absorbed%20by%20the%20Emergency%2C%20working%20underground.%20He%20was%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20disseminating%20information%2C%20including%20counter-propaganda%20against%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20(and%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s)%20dictatorial%20regime.%20He%20also%20took%20care%20of%20the%20families%20of%20those%20RSS%20leaders%20who%20were%20in%20prison%20and%20maintained%20%E2%80%9Clinks%20between%20Indians%20abroad%20and%20at%20home%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20Emergency%2C%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cassigned%20the%20role%20of%20key%20researcher%20for%20a%20resource%20book%20on%20the%20Emergency%E2%80%9D.%20This%20episode%20is%20important%20because%20it%20enabled%20Modi%20not%20only%20to%20interact%20with%20many%20politicians%2C%20but%20also%20to%20tour%20India.%20But%20he%20soon%20returned%20to%20his%20home%20state%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20within%20the%20local%20RSS.%20As%20early%20as%201978%20he%20had%20been%20appointed%20vibhag%20pracharak%20(the%20head%20of%20RSS%20units%20in%20six%20districts)%2C%20and%20then%20sambhag%20pracharak%20(which%20involved%20the%20supervision%20of%20two%20vibhags%2C%20or%20divisions%2C%20those%20of%20Surat%20and%20Baroda).%20In%201981%2C%20he%20became%20prant%20pracharak%2C%20a%20role%20that%20consisted%20in%20coordinating%20various%20organisations%20of%20the%20Sangh%2C%20including%20the%20Vishva%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Kisan%20Sangh%20and%20the%20ABVP%20throughout%20Gujarat.%20By%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%20he%20had%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20skilled%20organiser%20and%2C%20when%20in%201986%20L.K.%20Advani%20became%20BJP%20president%2C%20he%20considered%20taking%20Modi%20on%20for%20party%20work.%20Deputed%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%201987%2C%20he%20became%20the%20sangathan%20mantri%20(organising%20secretary)%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20unit%20of%20the%20party.The%20organising%20secretaries%20had%20formed%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20since%20the%201950s%2C%20after%20Deendayal%20Upadhyaya%20created%20the%20post%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20occupied%20it%20for%20years%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20As%20the%20state%20party%20organiser-in-chief%2C%20Modi%20was%20the%20architect%20of%20a%20whole%20series%20of%20programmes%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9CYatras%E2%80%9D%20(literally%20pilgrimages%20or%20processions%2C%20but%20in%20practice%20mass%20demonstrations).%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Nyay%20Yatra%20(Justice%20Pilgrimage)%20aimed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdemand%20justice%20for%20Hindu%20riot%20victims%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20Lok%20Shakti%20Yatra%20(People%E2%80%99s%20Power%20Pilgrimage)%20mobilised%20street%20protests%20against%20the%20liquor%20mafia%20in%20the%20Old%20City%20of%20Ahmedabad%20%E2%80%93%20a%20demonstration%20that%20exemplified%20the%20strategy%20of%20polarisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20Modi%20managed%20the%20Gujarat%20leg%20of%20Advani%E2%80%99s%201990%20Rath%20Yatra%2C%20which%20started%20from%20Somnath.%20Subsequently%2C%20his%20skills%20as%20an%20organiser%20were%20used%20for%20Yatra%20politics%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20In%20late%201991%2C%20he%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Ekta%20Yatra%2C%20which%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%2C%20the%20BJP%20president%20who%20had%20just%20taken%20over%20from%20Advani%2C%20led%20from%20Kanyakumari%20to%20Srinagar%20in%20order%20to%20reaffirm%20the%20national%20unity%20of%20India.%20His%20colleagues%20in%20the%20BJP%20office%20in%20Delhi%20noticed%20that%20on%20this%20occasion%20%E2%80%9Che%20did%20not%20function%20the%20way%20a%20full-time%20RSS%20pracharak%20should.%20He%20was%20seen%20as%20projecting%20himself%20and%20seeking%20the%20limelight.%E2%80%9D%20Indeed%2C%20during%20the%20EktaYatra%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20only%20was%20Modi%20accompanying%20Joshiji%20on%20his%20vehicle%2C%20but%20would%2C%20at%20every%20stop%2C%20address%20the%20crowds%20along%20with%20the%20BJP%20president.As%20an%20organiser%20of%20the%20yatra%2C%20he%20should%20have%20consciously%20kept%20a%20low%20profile.%E2%80%9D%20Besides%20his%20taste%20for%20interacting%20with%20the%20Indian%20public%20which%20the%20EktaYatra%20revealed%2C%20it%20also%20afforded%20him%20a%20new%20opportunity%20to%20broaden%20his%20national%2C%20pan-Indian%20political%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20becoming%20the%20main%20party%20organiser%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20Modi%20concentrated%20on%20one%20particular%20objective%20in%20the%201980s%3A%20the%20conquest%20of%20local%20power%20structures.%20He%20had%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20route%20to%20Gandhinagar%20went%20through%20local%20power%20structures%20that%20had%20to%20be%20won%E2%80%9D.%20As%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20BJP%20took%20the%20municipality%20of%20Rajkot%20in%201983%20and%20that%20of%20Ahmedabad%20four%20years%20later%2C%20when%20Modi%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20all%20BJP%20election%20campaigns%20in%20the%20state%2C%20including%20local%20ones.%20These%20successes%20were%20achieved%20largely%20thanks%20to%20the%20growing%20political%20polarisation%20resulting%20from%20communal%20violence.Ahmedabad%20is%20a%20case%20in%20point.The%20BJP%20rose%20to%20power%20there%20after%20the%201985%20conflagration%2C%20before%20which%20Modi%20had%20told%20his%20professor%2C%20Pravin%20Sheth%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMuslims%20are%20spreading%20fear%20among%20the%20mixed%20localities%20of%20walled%20city%20areas%20in%20Ahmedabad.%20Their%20intention%20is%20to%20force%20evict%2070%25%20of%20Hindu%20population%20out%20of%20the%20pols%20%5Blanes%20of%20the%20Old%20City%20forming%20sub-local%20communities%5D%20in%20the%20walled%20city%20by%20spreading%20fear%2C%20and%20put%20the%20rest%20in%20minority%20so%20that%20they%20also%20sell%20their%20houses%20to%20Muslims%20and%20migrate%20to%20safer%20places%20in%20despair.%20Thus%2C%20they%20plan%20to%20convert%20the%20entire%20area%20of%20the%20walled%20city%20into%20a%20Muslim%20dominated%20town.%20But%20our%20RSS%20volunteers%20have%20reached%20there.%20We%20will%20educate%20Hindus%20about%20Muslim%20intent%2C%20try%20to%20raise%20their%20morale%20and%20prevent%20them%20from%20being%20evicted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sangh%20Parivar%20was%20indeed%20effective%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20as%20large%20numbers%20of%20Muslims%20fled%20during%20the%201985%20riots%20and%20sought%20refuge%20in%20the%20ghetto%20of%20Juhapura.%20But%20the%20polarisation%20strategy%20worked%20elsewhere%3B%20and%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20in%201995%20the%20BJP%20won%20six%20municipal%20corporations%2C%20including%20that%20of%20Surat%20where%20the%20BJP%20took%20all%20the%20seats.The%20party%20also%20won%20a%20majority%20in%2018%20of%2019%20District%20Panchayat%20boards.%20Achyut%20Yagnik%20and%20Suchitra%20Sheth%20point%20out%20that%20in%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20state%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20crucial%20factor%20was%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%E2%80%99s%20penetration%20into%20the%20local%20power%20structures%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20which%20began%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20continued%20in%20the%201990s%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20Modi%20appeared%20as%20a%20major%20architect%20of%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%20after%20the%20party%20for%20the%20first%20time%20won%20a%20majority%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20Assembly.%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20continued%20to%20rely%20on%20communal%20polarisation%2C%20a%20process%20that%20was%20nurtured%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%201985%20riot%2C%20by%20targeting%20the%20%E2%80%9CMuslim%20mafia%E2%80%9D%20of%20Abdul%20Latif.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20was%20also%20successful%20in%20eliminating%20political%20rivals%20and%20winning%20powerful%20patrons%20in%20Delhi%2C%20as%20the%201996%20episode%20of%20Advani%E2%80%99s%20election%20in%20Gandhinagar%20shows.The%20BJP%20president%20was%20then%20looking%20for%20a%20safe%20berth%2C%20given%20that%20in%201991%20he%20had%20won%20his%20New%20Delhi%20seat%20by%20a%20small%20margin%3A%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20Modi%20who%20suggested%20to%20Advani%20that%20he%20should%20contest%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%20Gandhinagar%20%E2%80%A6%20that%20was%20until%20then%20represented%20by%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20peer-turned-foe%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20(he%20won%20in%201989).%20It%20was%20a%20masterstroke%20as%20BJP%20got%20charged%20up%20in%20the%20state%20and%20Vaghela%20was%20relegated%20to%20the%20fringes.The%20relationship%20grew%20with%20Advani%20frequently%20visiting%20Gujarat%20after%20becoming%20MP%20from%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%20Modi%20had%20killed%20two%20birds%20with%20one%20stone%2C%20displaying%20a%20political%20acumen%20that%20is%20not%20usually%20the%20main%20hallmark%20of%20RSS%20pracharaks%2C%20who%20make%20a%20point%20of%20eschewing%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20by%20definition%2C%20a%20dirty%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20Modi%20became%20a%20semi-public%20figure%2C%20to%20such%20an%20extent%20that%20he%20was%20called%20%E2%80%9Csuper%20chief%20minister%E2%80%9D%20after%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20formed%20the%20government%20and%20became%20its%20official%20head.%20He%20took%20part%20in%20cabinet%20meetings%20and%20remained%20in%20the%20room%20when%20senior%20bureaucrats%20came%20to%20report%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Modi%20failed%20to%20keep%20the%20party%20united%2C%20despite%20this%20being%20a%20major%20responsibility%20of%20a%20sangathan%20mantri.%20After%20the%201995%20electoral%20triumph%2C%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20and%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20were%20locked%20in%20fierce%20rivalry%20for%20the%20post%20of%20chief%20minister.%20In%20spite%20of%20his%20close%20long-term%20relationship%20with%20the%20latter%20(Vaghela%20was%2C%20like%20him%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20low-caste%20RSS%20veterans%20and%20party%20president%20when%20Modi%20was%20his%20secretary)%2C%20Modi%20threw%20his%20weight%20behind%20Patel%2C%20ensuring%20that%20Vaghela%20would%20get%20none%20of%20the%20spoils%20that%20were%20distributed%20to%20party%20workers.%20This%20move%20further%20alienated%20Vaghela%2C%20who%20created%20a%20difficult%20situation%20for%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20after%20defecting%20with%20%E2%80%9Chis%E2%80%9D%2047%20MLAs%20as%20mentioned%20above.%20After%20this%20episode%2C%20Patel%2C%20who%20came%20increasingly%20under%20the%20influence%20of%20Sanjay%20Joshi%2C%20another%20pracharak%20assigned%20to%20the%20BJP%20who%20was%20also%20a%20rival%20of%20Modi%2C%20persuaded%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%20leaders%20that%20Modi%20had%20to%20be%20banished%20from%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203846%2FNarendra_Modi_and_Prime_Minister_Atal_Bihari_Vajpayee_in_New_Delhi_in_October_12_2001.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22409%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696450%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22304%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%20with%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%202001.%20Photo%3A%20PMO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Modi%20went%20to%20Delhi%20when%20he%20was%20appointed%20national%20secretary%20in%20November%201995%2C%20in%20charge%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%20Advani%2C%20who%20had%20become%20BJP%20president%20again%20in%201993%2C%20had%20been%20keen%20to%20promote%20him%20to%20that%20post%2C%20but%20his%20increasingly%20influential%20right-hand%20man%2C%20Pramod%20Mahajan%2C%20did%20not%20see%20eye%20to%20eye%20with%20Modi%2C%20and%20Modi%20had%20to%20spend%20most%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Chandigarh.%20However%2C%20when%20Kushabhau%20Thakre%2C%20another%20pracharak%20turned%20BJP%20cadre%2C%20became%20party%20president%20in%201998%2C%20Modi%20was%20promoted%20to%20the%20post%20of%20general%20secretary%20and%20started%2C%20from%20Delhi%2C%20to%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20organisation%20with%20official%20responsibilities%20for%20the%20states%20of%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Chandigarh%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Bharatiya%20JanataYuva%20Morcha%20(the%20youth%20wing%20of%20the%20party).%20He%20was%20retained%20in%20this%20capacity%20by%20Bangaru%20Laxman%20when%20the%20latter%20took%20over%20from%20Thakre%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20biographers%20M.V.%20Kamath%20and%20K.%20Randeri%20emphasise%20that%20by%20becoming%20Bharatiya%20sangathan%20mahamantri%2C%20Modi%20was%20following%20in%20the%20steps%20of%20three%20prestigious%20figures%3A%20Deendayal%20Upadhyaya%2C%20S.S.%20Bhandari%20and%20Kushabhau%20Thakre.%20However%2C%20none%20of%20them%20became%20public%20figures%20in%20the%20way%20he%20did%3A%20as%20organisers%2C%20they%20remained%20the%20power%20behind%20the%20throne%2C%20even%20though%20Upadhyaya%20and%20Thakre%20contested%20elections%20once%2C%20by%20default.%20Modi%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20had%20evinced%20some%20interest%20in%20the%20life%20of%20a%20politician.%20He%20liked%20public%20meetings%20and%20interacting%20with%20both%20the%20masses%20and%20the%20media.%20Other%20differences%20pertained%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tendency%20to%20side%20in%20faction%20fights%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20party%20unity%20and%20his%20abrupt%20behaviour%20with%20colleagues%2C%20two%20things%20that%20precipitated%20long-lasting%20antagonisms.%20Modi%20made%20two%20enemies%20in%20the%201990s%3A%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20and%20Sanjay%20Joshi.%20Pravin%20Sheth%20attributed%20these%20developments%20to%20%E2%80%9Chis%20egoistic%20nature%20and%20abrasive%20behaviour%20with%20his%20fellow%20workers.%20Sometimes%20it%20appears%20that%20he%20has%20a%20Hubris%20complex.%20In%20this%20state%2C%20he%20tends%20to%20believe%20that%20his%20level%20of%20understanding%20is%20more%20than%20anyone%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20Modi%20played%20the%20politician%E2%80%99s%20game%20when%20it%20served%20his%20interests.%20Not%20only%20did%20he%20sidelineVaghela%20by%20suggesting%20to%20Advani%20that%20he%20stand%20for%20his%20constituency%2C%20but%20he%20also%20tried%20to%20dislodge%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat.%20In%20his%20memoirs%2C%20Vinod%20Mehta%2C%20then%20editor-in-chief%20of%20Outlook%2C%20recalls%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20he%20was%20working%20at%20the%20party%20office%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20came%20to%20see%20me%20in%20the%20office.%20He%20brought%20along%20some%20documents%20that%20indicated%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20Keshubhai%20Patel%2C%20was%20up%20to%20no%20good.The%20next%20thing%20I%20heard%20was%20that%20he%20had%20become%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20place%20of%20Keshubhai.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20Modi%20continued%20to%20present%20himself%20as%20an%20organisation%20man%20par%20excellence%20and%2C%20when%20Vajpayee%20asked%20him%20to%20take%20over%20from%20Keshubhai%20Patel%2C%20he%20replied%3A%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20not%20my%20work.%20I%20have%20been%20away%20from%20Gujarat%20for%20six%20long%20years.%20I%20am%20not%20familiar%20with%20the%20issues.%20What%20will%20I%20do%20there%3F%20It%20is%20not%20a%20field%20of%20my%20liking%20%5Bmy%20emphasis%5D.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20anyone.%E2%80%9D%20Although%20he%20liked%20mass%20meetings%2C%20Modi%20did%20not%20consider%20himself%20a%20politician.This%20factor%20was%20to%20play%20a%20role%20when%20he%20took%20his%20first%20steps%20as%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%2085%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20be%20a%20challenging%20task%20to%20arrest%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20declining%20trend%20before%20the%20state%20elections%20that%20were%20due%20to%20be%20held%20in%20February%202003.%20Just%20before%20his%20swearing-in%20as%20chief%20minister%20he%20told%20his%20colleagues%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20only%20500%20days%20and%2012%2C000%20hours%20before%20the%20next%20election%20for%20the%20state%20assembly.%E2%80%9D%20That%20the%20BJP%20was%20under%20such%20pressure%20probably%20explains%20why%20communal%20polarisation%20appeared%20particularly%20relevant%20to%20its%20pursuit%20of%20power%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fchristophe-jaffrelot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristophe%20Jaffrelot%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%20at%20CERI-Sciences%20Po%2FCNRS%2C%20Paris%2C%20Professor%20of%20Indian%20Politics%20and%20Sociology%20at%20King%E2%80%99s%20College%20London%20and%20Chair%20of%20the%20British%20Association%20for%20South%20Asian%20St