22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c23b5243bb77284ba3e4a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221367%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink%20carried%20out%20its%20first%20human%20brain%20implant%20in%20January%2C%20with%20the%20patient%20said%20to%20be%20recovering%20well%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1752098683024220632%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20says%20its%20initial%20goal%20is%20to%20find%20a%20way%20of%20allowing%20humans%20to%20control%20a%20computer%20keyboard%20or%20cursor%20with%20their%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-shifts-delaware-nevada-musk-rails-against-pay-ruling-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707656446000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c89e7c6fcb546d2d4e4bf0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-shifts-delaware-nevada-musk-rails-against-pay-ruling-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20comes%20after%20a%20Delaware%20judge%20denied%20Musk%20a%20%2455%20billion%20pay%20package.%20%26quot%3BNever%20incorporate%20your%20company%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Delaware%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nrennolds%40insider.com%20(Nathan%20Rennolds)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-shifts-delaware-nevada-musk-rails-against-pay-ruling-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20'Likely%20to%20be%20Sold'%20Ahead%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls.%20Will%20the%20SC%20Act%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20clause%208%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%202018%2C%20bonds%20can%20be%20issued%20for%2010%20days%20each%20in%20January%2C%20April%2C%20July%20and%20October%2C%20and%20an%20additional%2030%20days%20in%20the%20year%20of%20a%20general%20election.%20With%20general%20elections%202024%20just%20months%20away%2C%20the%2030-day%20period%20of%20issuance%20of%20bonds%20might%20be%20invoked%20again%2C%20even%20though%20the%20whole%20scheme%20has%20been%20challenged%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2002%2C%202023%2C%20the%20SC%20hearing%20in%20the%20matter%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fdonor-anonymity-versus-voters-right-to-know-supreme-court-reserves-judgment-in-electoral-bonds-case%2F%5C%22%3Ecompleted%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20judgment%20was%20reserved.%20In%20its%20order%20of%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20the%20SC%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20that%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20any%20event%2C%20we%20now%20direct%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20shall%20produce%20up-to-date%20data%20until%2030%20September%202023%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20interim%20directions%20which%20were%20issued%20on%2012%20April%202019.%20The%20exercise%20shall%20be%20carried%20out%20on%20or%20before%2019%20November%202023.%20The%20data%20in%20sealed%20packet%20shall%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Registrar%20(judicial)%20of%20this%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransparency%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra%20filed%20an%20RTI%20with%20the%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20(PIO)%20of%20the%20ECI%20in%20the%20third%20week%20of%20November%202023%2C%20requesting%20copies%20of%20the%20complete%20set%20of%20documents%20including%20notings%20in%20the%20file(s)%2Ffolders%20on%20which%20Commission%20(EC)%20had%20processed%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20SC%20order%20of%20November%202%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20brought%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20PIO%20that%20he%20had%20filed%20a%20similar%20RTI%20request%20even%20after%20the%20SC%20order%20of%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20and%20had%20been%20provided%20complete%20file%20documents%20including%20a%20list%20of%20105%20political%20parties%20which%20provided%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20sealed%20cover%20to%20the%20EC.%20Batra%20attached%20that%20list%20with%20his%20current%20RTI%20application%2C%20adding%20that%20in%20October%202023%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20in%20response%20to%20an%20RTI%20application%2C%20had%20said%20that%20only%2025%20political%20parties%20had%20opened%20accounts%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20encashing%20these%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20mentioned%20that%20as%20per%20the%20existing%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%20(EB)%20is%20a%20promissory%20note%20(akin%20to%20currency%20note)%20%E2%80%93%20hence%20the%20SBI%20would%20have%20details%20of%20EBs%20buyers%2Fdonors%20as%20per%20their%20KYC%20(Know%20Your%20Customer%20protocol).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESBI%20would%20also%20have%20details%20of%20%E2%80%98political%20party%20account%E2%80%99%20in%20which%20the%20said%20EB%20is%20redeemed%2C%20because%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%20(EB)%20has%20a%20hidden%20number%20verified%20by%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20authorised%20branch%20before%20redemption%20in%20a%20political%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98specific%20account%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20opened%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20redeeming%20electoral%20bonds.%20Legally%2C%20the%20political%20party%20would%20not%20know%20the%20name%20of%20the%20donor%20based%20solely%20on%20the%20anonymous%20promissory%20note%20termed%20%E2%80%98electoral%20bond%E2%80%99%20it%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%202019%2C%20Commodore%20Batra%20sought%20the%20%E2%80%98List%20of%20Political%20Parties%E2%80%99%20which%20had%20submitted%20EB%20details%20to%20ECI%20in%20sealed%20covers%2C%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20letter%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20dated%20November%203%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20on%20December%2018%2C%202023%2C%20Binod%20Kumar%2C%20the%20public%20information%20officer%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20denied%20information%20under%20the%20Section-8(1)(b)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20noteworthy%20the%20Section-8(1)(b)%20of%20the%20act%20mentions%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%20which%20has%20been%20expressly%20forbidden%20to%20be%20published%20by%20any%20court%20of%20law%20or%20tribunal%20or%20the%20disclosure%20of%20which%20may%20constitute%20contempt%20of%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20filed%20an%20appeal%20against%20this%20denial%20of%20information%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20not%20forbidden%20publication%20of%20the%20information.%20Commodore%20Batra%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20PIO%20had%20also%20failed%20to%20offer%20a%20cogent%20reason%20for%20denying%20the%20information.%20While%20the%20PIO%20under%20section%207(1)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005%20quoted%20Section-8(1)(b)%20for%20denial%20of%20information%2C%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20provide%20justification%20for%20arriving%20at%20the%20reason%20for%20denial%2C%20as%20envisaged%20under%20the%20Section%207(8)(i)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20this%20reporter%2C%20Commodore%20Batra%20noted%20that%20two%20days%20after%20the%20SC%20reserved%20judgment%2C%20on%20November%204%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20announced%2015%20days%20of%20sale%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20from%20November%206-20%2C%202023.%20Electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20again%20for%2010%20days%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20apex%20court%20directed%20the%20ECI%20to%20produce%20up-to-date%20data%20until%20September%2030%2C%202023%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20interim%20directions%20issued%20on%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20it%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20bonds%20have%20been%20sold%20already%20for%20a%20period%20of%2045%20days%20after%20September%2030%2C%202023.%20(10%20days%20in%20October%2C%2015%20days%20in%20November%202023%20and%2010%20days%20in%20January%202014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Electoral%20Bond%20scheme%20is%20problematic%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20kill%20democracy%20by%20offering%20undue%20advantage%20to%20the%20party%20in%20power%20%E2%80%93%20between%20March%202018%20and%20September%202023%2C%20the%20bonds%20were%20sold%20in%2030%20phases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20bonds%20sold%20are%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20each%20%E2%80%93%20clearly%2C%20these%20bonds%20are%20becoming%20the%20major%20source%20of%20electoral%20funding%2C%20and%20are%20being%20purchased%20by%20the%20very%20rich%2C%20or%20corporate%20players%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20average%20Indian.%20Only%200.0001%25%20of%20the%20bonds%20were%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%2C000.%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2F57-vs-10-bjp-vs-congress-share-in-electoral-bond-funds-9007429%2F%5C%22%3Evast%20majority%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20these%20bonds%20(57%25)%20also%20go%20to%20the%20party%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20question%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20on%20February%205%2C%202024%2C%20Pankaj%20Chaudhary%2C%20Union%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Finance%20answered%20that%20Electoral%20Bonds%20worth%20Rs16%2C518%20crore%20had%20so%20far%20been%20purchased%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20The%20government%20had%20paid%20SBI%20Rs%208.57%20crore%20as%20commission%2C%20and%20Security%20Printing%20and%20Minting%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Limited%20had%20received%20Rs%201.90%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20the%20ordinary%20Indian%20bears%20this%20expense%20that%20the%20government%20shoulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20the%20Union%20minister%20explained%20that%20the%20objective%20of%20the%20scheme%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20%E2%80%9Cclean%2C%20tax%20paid%20money%20is%20coming%20into%20the%20system%20of%20political%20funding%20through%20proper%20banking%20channel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EHowever%2C%20as%20has%20been%20speculated%2C%20since%20the%20bonds%20are%20anonymous%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20for%20them%20to%20change%20hands%20several%20times%20before%20being%20submitted%20to%20a%20political%20party%20for%20encashment%20%E2%80%93%20who%20can%20guarantee%20that%20black%20money%20is%20not%20turned%20white%20through%20this%20scheme%2C%20as%20a%20man%20holding%20a%20bond%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20value%20could%20sell%20it%20to%20someone%20else%20at%2C%20say%2C%20Rs%201.2%20crore%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20favour%20of%20turning%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20of%20black%20money%20white%3F%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Affairs%20has%20referred%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fgovt-spent-rs-13-50-cr-to-operate-electoral-bond-scheme-9089091%2F%5C%22%3Ecorrespondence%3C%2Fa%3E%20showing%20that%2018%25%20GST%20is%20charged%20on%20the%20bonds%2C%20but%20reimbursed%20by%20the%20government%20to%20SBI%3B%20what%20this%20means%20is%20that%20the%20burden%20is%20borne%20entirely%20by%20the%20Indian%20citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Electoral%20Bond%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20through%20amendments%20to%20law%20that%20lifted%20restrictions%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20donations%20that%20private%20firms%20could%20make%3B%20Election%20Commission%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%202017%2C%20underlined%20that%20the%20proposal%20to%20lift%20the%20limit%20on%20donations%20from%20companies%20%E2%80%9Copens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20shell%20companies%20being%20set%20up%20for%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20making%20donations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirms%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20declare%20which%20party%20they%20are%20contributing%20to%3B%20transparency%20in%20fund-raising%20by%20political%20parties%20is%20compromised%20as%20no%20reporting%20of%20contributions%20received%20is%20expected%20from%20the%20political%20parties.%20Donations%20can%20also%20be%20received%20from%20foreign%20companies%20having%20majority%20stake%20in%20Indian%20firms%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20lead%20to%20Indian%20policies%20being%20influenced%20by%20foreign%20companies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20rule%20in%20this%20matter%20with%20some%20urgency%2C%20the%20Centre%20may%20declare%20another%20round%20of%2030-day%20issuance%20of%20the%20bond%2C%20in%20different%20phases%2C%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERosamma%20Thomas%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.counterview.net%2F2024%2F02%2Fwill-more-electoral-bonds-be-sold-ahead.html%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20Counterview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707656408000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-likely-to-be-sold-ahead-of-lok-sabha-polls-will-the-sc-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20rule%20in%20this%20matter%20with%20some%20urgency%2C%20the%20Centre%20may%20declare%20another%20round%20of%2030-day%20issuance%20of%20the%20bond%2C%20in%20different%20phases%2C%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-likely-to-be-sold-ahead-of-lok-sabha-polls-will-the-sc-act%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20have%20the%20same%20last%20name%20as%