%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20for%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20prepared%20by%20the%20Land%20Resources%20Department%20and%20approved%20by%20the%20state%20cabinet%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20news%20report%2C%20dated%20February%2011%2C%20said.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20the%20objective%20is%20to%20establish%20%E2%80%9Can%20institutional%20mechanism%20to%20enforce%20correct%20use%20of%20names%20of%20places%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20to%20%E2%80%9Clay%20down%20procedures%20for%20giving%20names%20to%20places%2C%20and%20also%20for%20altering%20names%20of%20places%E2%80%9D.%20Per%20the%20Bill%2C%20offenders%20will%20be%20punished%20with%20a%20penalty%2C%20and%20can%20receive%20one%20to%20three%20years%20of%20imprisonment%20upon%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20new%20Bill%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98Place%20Names%20Committee%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20created%20to%20make%20recommendations%20on%20the%20names%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20latest%20news%20report%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20proposal%20for%20the%20Act%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20multiple%20instances%20of%20the%20use%20of%20unauthorised%20names%20of%20places%20by%20certain%20individuals%20or%20groups%20of%20people%20or%20organisations%2C%20with%20possible%20malafide%20intent%2C%20which%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20create%20confusion%20in%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%20The%20proposal%20also%20lists%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccertain%20administrative%20challenges%20are%20also%20faced%20due%20to%20such%20unauthorised%20use%20of%20names%20of%20places%20at%20the%20time%20of%20discharging%20their%20duties%20by%20government%20officials%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENames%20of%20places%20have%20been%20a%20contested%20issue%20since%20violence%20began%20in%20Manipur%20in%20May%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20report%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20prominent%20example%E2%80%9D%20is%20that%20of%20the%20Kuki-Zomi-dominated%20district%20Churachandpur%20and%20its%20district%20headquarters%2C%20also%20called%20Churachandpur.%20The%20district%20and%20town%20is%20named%20after%20a%20Meitei%20king%20of%20the%20former%20Manipur%20kingdom%2C%20Churachand%20Singh%2C%20who%20ruled%20the%20area%20from%201891%20to%201941.%20But%20people%20from%20the%20Kuki-Zomi%20community%20have%20been%20calling%20the%20town%20%E2%80%9CLamka%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Both%20the%20names%20are%20over%20a%20hundred%20years%20old%2C%20per%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20after%20the%20violence%20erupted%2C%20the%20name%20Lamka%20began%20appearing%20on%20homes%2C%20shops%20and%20even%20government%20institutions%20and%20offices.%20Similarly%2C%20resident%20Meiteis%20now%20call%20Paite%20Veng%20(Paite%20is%20a%20Zo%20sub-tribe%20and%20Veng%20means%20colony)%20in%20Imphal%20%E2%80%98Kwakeithel%20Ningthemkol%E2%80%99%20via%20a%20signboard%2C%20the%20news%20report%20highlighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Manipur%20government%2C%20via%20an%20order%20by%20the%20chief%20secretary%2C%20told%20organisations%20and%20individuals%20to%20not%20change%20names%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdistricts%2C%20sub-divisions%2C%20places%2C%20institutions%2C%20and%20addresses%20of%20such%20institutions%E2%80%9D%20on%20their%20own%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20create%20possible%20conflict%20between%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fdont-change-names-of-places-warns-manipur-government%2Farticle67393496.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20assembly%20session%20will%20be%20only%20the%20second%20so%20far%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20ethnic%20conflict%20on%20May%203%20last%20year.%20As%20per%20latest%20official%20figures%20%E2%80%93%20as%20of%20September%2015%20last%20year%20%E2%80%93%20the%20violence%20has%20killed%20175%20people%20and%20injured%201%2C118%3B%2032%20people%20are%20still%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707650780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18103704%2FF6AFcQWaIAIi2H2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanging-place-names-may-soon-be-punishable-in-manipur-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Bill%20that%20proposes%20this%20will%20likely%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Manipur%20assembly%20session.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanging-place-names-may-soon-be-punishable-in-manipur-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Xiaomi%20says%20India's%20scrutiny%20of%20Chinese%20firms%20unnerves%20suppliers%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707650683000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-06%2F30%2Ffull%2F1593533232-6474.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fxiaomi-says-india-s-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerves-suppliers-report-124021100349_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20letter%2C%20Xiaomi%20India%20President%20Muralikrishnan%20B.%20said%20India%20needed%20to%20work%20on%20'confidence%20building'%20measures%20to%20encourage%20component%20suppliers%20to%20setup%20operations%20locally%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fxiaomi-says-india-s-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerves-suppliers-report-124021100349_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fxiaomi-says-india-s-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerves-suppliers-report-124021100349_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bus