A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fpdredge%2Fpdr-edge-frm-asst-sec-080320.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMost%20people%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20suburbanites%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20that%20likely%20won%E2%80%99t%20change%20anytime%20soon.%20Ideally%2C%20the%20suburbs%20offer%20the%20best%20of%20both%20the%20urban%20and%20rural%20worlds%3A%20a%20white%20picket%20fence%20within%20reach%20of%20downtown%20jobs%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sprawl%20has%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinherent%20geometry%20problem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Andrew%20Justus%2C%20a%20housing-policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20Niskanen%20Center%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank.%20As%20a%20suburb%20or%20exurb%20grows%20to%20accommodate%20more%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20are%20mostly%20limited%20to%20detached%20single-family%20houses%20%E2%80%94%20roads%20grow%2C%20cars%20multiply%2C%20and%20the%20distance%20between%20someone%E2%80%99s%20house%20and%20their%20job%2C%20school%2C%20or%20grocery%20store%20stretches.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20end%20up%20with%20suburbs%20that%20are%20neither%20close%20to%20the%20outskirts%20nor%20close%20to%20the%20city%20center%E2%80%9D%20and%20residents%20are%20%E2%80%9Ctrapped%20between%E2%80%9D%20the%20two%20worlds%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justus%20said.%20This%20is%20how%20suburbs%20got%20their%20bad%20reputation%20as%20isolating%2C%20boring%2C%20and%20unsustainable.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20for%20urbanists%2C%20housing%20advocates%2C%20and%20anyone%20who%20cares%20about%20climate%20change%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20the%20communities%20most%20Americans%20live%20in%20healthier%20for%20their%20inhabitants%20and%20the%20planet.%20This%20is%20where%20a%20kind%20of%20decentralized%20urbanism%20comes%20in.%20Experts%20say%20the%20solution%20is%20to%20make%20suburbs%20denser%2C%20more%20walkable%2C%20and%20more%20mixed-use%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0essentially%20more%20like%20traditional%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20meet%20people%20where%20they%20live%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Adie%20Tomer%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20infrastructure%20policy%20and%20urban%20economics%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExclusive%2C%20isolating%2C%20and%20inconvenient%20suburbs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20suburbs%20have%20always%20been%20flawed%20in%20a%20host%20of%20ways.%20Beginning%20in%20the%20mid-19th%20century%2C%20new%20suburbs%20helped%20white%20families%20build%20wealth%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Ftrend-1-separate-and-unequal-neighborhoods-are-sustaining-racial-and-economic-injustice-in-the-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenforcing%20racial%20segregation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20of%20the%201960s%20and%2070s%20and%20the%20early%20years%20of%20integration%2C%20suburbs%20facilitated%20white%20flight.%20While%20many%20more%20people%20of%20color%20live%20outside%20cities%20today%2C%20they%20largely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Ftrump-is-clinging-to-an-outdated-vision-of-americas-suburbs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edon%E2%80%99t%20live%20in%20the%20same%20suburban%20communities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20white%20people.%20Racial%20segregation%20used%20to%20be%20enforced%20explicitly%20by%20the%20law.%C2%A0Now%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnextcity.org%2Furbanist-news%2Fapartheid-by-another-name-how-zoning-regulations-perpetuate-segregation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eperpetuated%20by%20policies%20like%20single-family%20zoning%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20more%20affordable%20multi-family%20housing%20in%20most%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20restrictive%20zoning%20is%20also%20what%20separates%20homes%20from%20everything%20else%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0making%20it%20illegal%20to%20put%20amenities%20like%20grocery%20stores%2C%20pharmacies%2C%20and%20restaurants%20in%20a%20residential%20neighborhood.%20Car-centric%20design%20is%20isolating%2C%20particularly%20for%20kids%2C%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20anyone%20else%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20drive.%20And%20an%20overreliance%20on%20cars%20has%20made%20vehicles%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fpublication%2F58861%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20top%20emitter%20of%20greenhouse%20gasses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20for%20the%20last%20several%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20American%20traveled%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bts.gov%2Fstatistical-products%2Fsurveys%2Fnational-household-travel-survey-daily-travel-quick-facts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etwice%20as%20many%20miles%20in%202017%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20did%20in%201969.%20The%20typical%20American%20lives%20seven%20miles%20from%20their%20local%20commercial%20hub.%20And%20just%2014%25%20of%20errands%20the%20median%20US%20resident%20makes%20are%20within%20a%2015-minute%20walk%20of%20where%20they%20live%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D959b27c8a83b66fc56e22b8df1a0641316fb436efae9121b50f66b9e09b96850%26postID%3D65c3b35dee61557013fb3b8b%26postSlug%3Dsuburbs-millennials-walkable-towns-cities-housing-affordability-loneliness-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41562-023-01770-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20recent%20study%20by%20MIT%20researchers%20found%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20exchange%20for%20individual%20land%20ownership%20at%20a%20historic%20scale%2C%20American%20suburbanites%20sacrifice%20key%20freedoms%2C%20including%20the%20freedom%20of%20movement%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20our%20most%20valuable%20asset%3A%20time%2C%20Tomer%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20County%20courthouse%20and%20Clocktower%20in%20the%20historic%20small%20town%20of%20Paoli%2C%20Indiana.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3b5e67a3d271488789158%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20view%20of%20the%20county%20courthouse%20and%20clocktower%20in%20the%20historic%20small%20town%20of%20Paoli%2C%20Indiana.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Sohm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20freedom%20of%20the%20small%20town%20or%20%E2%80%9815-minute%20city%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9C15-minute%20city%E2%80%9D%20is%20perhaps%20the%20buzziest%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20and%20most%20controversial%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0urban%20planning%20concept%20right%20now.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20ensure%20people%20can%20work%2C%20shop%2C%20and%20play%20within%20a%2015-minute%20walk%2C%20bike%2C%20or%20transit%20ride%20from%20where%20they%20live.%20But%20many%20conservatives%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-03-02%2Fhow-did-the-15-minute-city-get-tangled-up-in-a-far-right-conspiracy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edenounced%20it%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20socialist%20plan%20to%20strip%20people%20of%20their%20freedom%20and%20cars.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2015-minute%20cities%20aren%E2%80%99t%20new.%20They%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fa6f50b7c-f78f-469d-b3f2-c6f505edaa9c%3FaccessToken%3DzwAGCYwxPdhAkdOm9Qt8949GndOz8sb1Be2qnA.MEUCIQD-XoGUepLQ4s62PWEmDUGH8PCOndgUggaOlkIVAwtV4gIgYcoFGfY-grW59442ity5GNHT3AsL5FxgHbNCgZGGn_o%26sharetype%3Dgift%26token%3D17bcc7f1-3b6b-420f-b72b-7ffcb035b30d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enaturally%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20cities%20that%20allow%20for%20dense%2C%20mixed-use%20development%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they%20existed%20in%20America%E2%80%99s%20early%20suburbs%2C%20which%20were%20built%20around%20streetcars%2C%20rather%20than%20private%20vehicles.%20Because%20streetcars%20required%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20residential%20density%20to%20have%20sufficient%20ridership%2C%20those%20suburbs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0places%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnu.org%2Fpublicsquare%2Fcity-returns-its-streetcar-roots%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESomerville%2C%20Massachusetts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shakersquare.net%2Fhistory%2Fbefore-rapid.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShaker%20Heights%2C%20Ohio%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20much%20more%20like%20small%20cities%20or%20large%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20progressive%20and%20conservative%20urban%20experts%20can%20agree%20on%20one%20thing%3A%20the%20suburbs%20need%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoel%20Kotkin%2C%20a%20fellow%20in%20urban%20studies%20at%20Chapman%20University%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalreview.com%2F2024%2F01%2Flet-america-sprawl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecently%20expounded%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20virtues%20of%20sprawl%20in%20the%20conservative%20National%20Review%2C%20wants%20to%20see%20the%20country%20turn%20into%20an%20archipelago%20of%20villages%20or%20towns.%20He%20points%20to%20suburbs%20like%20Orange%2C%20California%2C%20Bronxville%20in%20Westchester%20County%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitthewoodlands.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Woodlands%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20master-planned%20suburb%20of%20Houston%20founded%20in%20the%201970s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKotkin%20says%20the%20American%20suburbs%20have%20%E2%80%9Cwon%20the%20battle%E2%80%9D%20with%20cities%2C%20reigning%20as%20the%20more%20economically%20and%20demographically%20dominant%20place.%20But%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20they%20haven't%20done%20is%20adjusted%20to%20that%20role%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Suburbs%20need%20to%20reinvent%20themselves%20to%20look%20more%20like%20towns%20or%20small%20cities%20to%20better%20%E2%80%9Csatisfy%20the%20urban%20appetites%20of%20their%20new%20residents%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetrofitting%20suburbs%20to%20look%20more%20like%20towns%20%E2%80%9Cis%20the%20opportunity%20to%20not%20have%20your%20cake%20and%20eat%20it%20too%20but%20about%20as%20close%20as%20you%20can%20get%20to%20it%20in%20an%20American%20context%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tomer%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProgressives%20agree.%20%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20of%20people%20think%20we're%20trying%20to%20limit%20freedom%20by%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20have%20more%20public%20transit%20and%20maybe%20fewer%20car-centric%20developments%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tayana%20Panova%2C%20an%20urban%20researcher%20writing%20a%20book%20about%20suburbia's%20effects%20on%20mental%20health.%20%E2%80%9CNo%2C%20we're%20trying%20to%20give%20you%20more%20freedom%20by%20giving%20you%20more%20options.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUrban%20planners%20say%20closer-in%2C%20streetcar%20suburbs%20with%20established%20downtowns%20are%20the%20easiest%20to%20transform%20into%20dense%2C%20walkable%20communities.%20But%20all%20kinds%20of%20suburbs%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20free%20themselves%20from%20traffic%20and%20long%20commutes%20and%20create%20more%20vibrant%20neighborhoods.%20Suburbs%20need%20to%20prioritize%20loosening%20zoning%20laws%2C%20building%20more%20dense%20housing%2C%20and%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20get%20places%20without%20a%20car%2C%20experts%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere's%20a%20core%20principle%2C%20which%20is%20start%20small%20and%20use%20the%20assets%20you've%20already%20got%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tomer%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20says%2C%20take%20an%20underused%20shopping%20center%20and%20put%20a%20market%20hall%20in%20it%2C%20build%20some%20multi-family%20housing%20nearby%2C%20and%20make%20the%20roads%20safer%20for%20pedestrians%20and%20bicyclists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETomer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fbuilding-for-proximity-the-role-of-activity-centers-in-reducing-total-miles-traveled%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%20in%20his%20recent%20study%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CBuilding%20for%20Proximity%2C%E2%80%9D%20that%20people%20in%20the%20110%20largest%20US%20metros%20who%20live%20within%20three%20miles%20of%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cactivity%20centers%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0recreation%20and%20shopping%20hubs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0drive%20much%20less%20than%20their%20more%20far-flung%20counterparts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20want%20to%20live%20in%20these%20types%20of%20neighborhoods.%20An%20analysis%20published%20last%20year%20found%20that%20homebuyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartgrowthamerica.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FFoot-Traffic-Ahead-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20the%2035%20biggest%20American%20metropolitan%20areas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20paid%2034%25%20more%20to%20live%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20while%20renters%20paid%2041%25%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20people%20are%20wanting%20these%20days%20is%20walkability%2C%E2%80%9D%20Panova%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20developers%2C%20if%20local%20governments%20and%20businesses%20are%20wise%20and%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20trends%20and%20what%20people%20are%20wanting%2C%20then%20they'll%20adapt%20to%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20places%2C%20this%20is%20already%20happening.%20A%20surge%20of%20millennial%20transplants%20are%20bringing%20their%20urban%20sensibilities%20to%20the%20city%20outskirts.%20Suburban%20retail%20is%20booming%20%E2%80%94%20half%20of%20Sweetgreen%20salad%20shops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fthe-decline-of-the-five-day-commute-is-a-boon-to-suburban-retail-55e4dc89%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eare%20now%20in%20the%20suburb