one%20market%20at%2018%25%2C%20also%20asked%20in%20the%20letter%20dated%20February%206%20that%20India%20consider%20offering%20manufacturing%20incentives%20and%20lowering%20import%20tariffs%20for%20certain%20smartphone%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20company%20assembles%20smartphones%20in%20India%20with%20mostly%20local%20components%20and%20the%20rest%20are%20imported%20from%20China%20and%20elsewhere.%20The%20letter%20is%20Xiaomi's%20response%20to%20a%20query%20from%20the%20IT%20Ministry%20asking%20how%20New%20Delhi%20can%20further%20develop%20the%20country's%20component%20manufacturing%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20ramped%20up%20scrutiny%20of%20Chinese%20businesses%20after%20a%202020%20border%20clash%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20killed%20at%20least%2020%20Indian%20soldiers%2C%20disrupting%20the%20investment%20plans%20of%20big%20Chinese%20companies%20and%20drawing%20repeated%20protests%20from%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Chinese%20companies%20operating%20in%20India%20are%20reticent%20to%20speak%20publicly%20about%20the%20scrutiny%2C%20Xiaomi's%20letter%20shows%20they%20continue%20to%20struggle%20in%20India%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20smartphone%20space%20where%20many%20critical%20components%20come%20from%20Chinese%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20Xiaomi%20India%20President%20Muralikrishnan%20B%20said%20India%20needed%20to%20work%20on%20%26quot%3Bconfidence%20building%26quot%3B%20measures%20to%20encourage%20component%20suppliers%20to%20set%20up%20operations%20locally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20apprehensions%20among%20component%20suppliers%20regarding%20establishing%20operations%20in%20India%2C%20stemming%20from%20the%20challenges%20faced%20by%20companies%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20from%20Chinese%20origin%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Muralikrishnan%20said%2C%20without%20naming%20any%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20said%20the%20concerns%20were%20related%20to%20compliance%20and%20visa%20issues%20that%20it%20didn't%20elaborate%20on%20and%20other%20factors.%20It%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20government%20should%20address%20these%20concerns%20and%20work%20to%20instil%20confidence%20among%20foreign%20component%20suppliers%2C%20encouraging%20them%20to%20set%20up%20manufacturing%20facilities%20in%20India.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXiaomi%20and%20the%20IT%20Ministry%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20queries%20for%20further%20information%20and%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20last%20year%20accused%20Chinese%20smartphone%20company%20Vivo%20Communication%20Technology%20of%20breaching%20some%20visa%20rules%20and%20alleged%20it%20siphoned%20%2413%20billion%20in%20funds%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20froze%20over%20%24600%20million%20in%20Xiaomi%20assets%20for%20alleged%20illegal%20remittances%20to%20foreign%20entities%20by%20passing%20them%20off%20as%20royalty%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Chinese%20companies%20deny%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20regulatory%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20likes%20of%20Xiaomi%20and%20Vivo%2C%20India%20has%20banned%20over%20300%20Chinese%20apps%20since%202020%2C%20including%20ByteDance's%20TikTok%2C%20and%20halted%20planned%20projects%20such%20as%20those%20planned%20by%20Chinese%20automakers%20BYD%20and%20Great%20Wall%20Motor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20source%20said%20many%20executives%20of%20Chinese%20electronics%20companies%20struggle%20to%20get%20visas%20to%20India%2C%20and%20their%20companies%20continue%20to%20face%20slow%20clearances%20for%20investments%20due%20to%20heavy%20scrutiny%20by%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20letter%2C%20Xiaomi's%20Muralikrishnan%20B%20also%20made%20a%20case%20for%20further%20lowering%20import%20tariffs%20just%20after%20New%20Delhi's%20January%2031%20move%20to%20reduce%20import%20taxes%20on%20battery%20covers%20and%20phone%20camera%20lenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EXiaomi%20has%20also%20asked%20India%20to%20reduce%20import%20tariffs%20on%20sub-components%20used%20in%20batteries%2C%20USB%20cables%2C%20and%20phone%20covers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReducing%20the%20import%20tariffs%20could%20%26quot%3Bincrease%20India's%20manufacturing%20competitiveness...%20in%20terms%20of%20costs%26quot%3B%2C%20Xiaomi%20said%20in%20the%20letter%2C%20but%20getting%20component%20manufacturers%20to%20set%20up%20shop%20in%20India%20would%20require%20bigger%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20top%20industrial%20policy%20bureaucrat%20Rajesh%20Kumar%20Singh%20signalled%20that%20India%20could%20ease%20its%20heightened%20scrutiny%20of%20Chinese%20investments%20if%20the%20two%20countries'%20border%20remains%20peaceful.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707649620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fd3m6h19_xiaomi-reuters_625x300_11_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fxiaomi-says-indias-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerving-suppliers-report-5037192%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China's%20Xiaomi%20has%20told%20New%20Delhi%20that%20smartphone%20component%20suppliers%20are%20wary%20about%20setting%20up%20operations%20in%20India%20amid%20heavy%20scrutiny%20of%20Chinese%20companies%20by%20the%20government%2C%20according%20to%20a%20letter%20and%20a%20source%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fxiaomi-says-indias-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerving-suppliers-report-5037192%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fxiaomi-says-indias-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerving-suppliers-report-5037192%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fxiaomi-says-indias-scrutiny-of-chinese-firms-unnerving-suppliers-report-5037192%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Neetu%20Kapoor%20Reacts%20To%20