%3EFormer%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20rallied%20his%20supporters%20from%20the%20jail%20as%20members%20of%20his%20party%2C%20contesting%20as%20independents%2C%20won%20101%20seats%20in%20the%20recently%20concluded%20Pakistan%20general%20elections.%20But%20the%20nation%20is%20still%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20as%20none%20of%20the%20parties%20managed%20to%20cross%20the%20133%20mark%20needed%20to%20form%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20now%20hinges%20on%20political%20horse-trading%2C%20as%20parties%20scramble%20to%20cobble%20together%20alliances%20to%20prove%20their%20majority.%20The%20odds%20seem%20stacked%20against%20PTI%2C%20with%20both%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20and%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%20inclined%20on%20keeping%20Imran%20Khan%20away%20from%20the%20country's%20top%20office%20at%20any%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20leaders%20have%20already%20launched%20alliance%20talks%2C%20but%20even%20with%20the%20combined%20strength%2C%20they%20will%20fall%20short%20of%20the%20majority%20by%206%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20coalition%2C%20if%20it%20happens%2C%20could%20have%20the%20upper%20hand%2C%20with%20Nawaz%20Sharif's%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PMLN)%20securing%2073%20seats%20and%20Bilawal%20Bhutto's%20Pakistan%20People's%20Party%20(PPP)%20winning%2054%20seats.%20Together%2C%20they%20fall%20six%20seats%20short%20of%20the%20133%20seats%20needed%20to%20form%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20tally%20was%20released%20over%2060%20hours%20after%20voting%20concluded%20in%20Thursday's%20national%20elections%2C%20a%20delay%20that%20has%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20ban%20and%20Imran%20Khan's%20imprisonment%20for%20convictions%20on%20charges%20ranging%20from%20leaking%20state%20secrets%20to%20corruption%20and%20an%20unlawful%20marriage%2C%20millions%20of%20the%20former%20cricketer's%20supporters%20came%20out%20to%20vote%20for%20him%2C%20even%20though%20he%20cannot%20be%20part%20of%20any%20government%20while%20he%20remains%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20disadvantage%20the%20independents%20face%20in%20trying%20to%20form%20a%20government%20is%20they%20are%20not%20eligible%20to%20be%20allocated%20any%20of%20parliament's%2070%20reserved%20seats%2C%20which%20are%20distributed%20according%20to%20party%20strength%20in%20the%20final%20tally.%20Sharif's%20party%20could%20get%20up%20to%2020%20of%20these%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20commission%20previously%20flagged%20that%20results%20for%20two%20seats%20could%20not%20yet%20be%20included%20-%20one%20in%20which%20a%20candidate%20was%20killed%20requiring%20the%20postponement%20of%20polling%2C%20and%20another%20in%20which%20polling%20would%20be%20completed%20later%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20political%20maneuvering%2C%20PTI%20has%20raised%20allegations%20of%20result%20tampering.%20Imran%20Khan's%20party%20has%20taken%20the%20matter%20to%20court%20and%20organised%20protests%20against%20the%20alleged%20manipulation.%20The%20coming%20days%20are%20crucial%2C%20as%20the%20nation%20watches%20closely%20to%20see%20how%20the%20political%20landscape%20unfolds%2C%20and%20whether%20a%20stable%20government%20can%20emerge%20in%20a%20country%20that%20is%20already%20struggling%20to%20recover%20from%20an%20economic%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707642120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fai76q7lo_imran-khan-pti_625x300_10_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-elections-explainer-despite-winning-most-seats-why-odds-are-against-imran-khan-party-in-pak-5036514%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20rallied%20his%20supporters%20from%20the%20jail%20as%20members%20of%20his%20party%2C%20contesting%20as%20independents%2C%20won%20101%20seats%20in%20the%20recently%20concluded%20Pakistan%20general%20elections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-elections-explainer-despite-winning-most-seats-why-odds-are-against-imran-khan-party-in-pak-5036514%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-elections-explainer-despite-winning-most-seats-why-odds-are-against-imran-khan-party-in-pak-5036514%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-elections-explainer-despite-winning-most-seats-why-odds-are-against-imran-khan-party-in-pak-5036514%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Translators%20Shouldn%E2%80%99t%20Feel%20Guilty%20About%20Modifying%20the%20Text%20to%20Make%20it%20Appealing'%3A%20Hansda%20Shekhar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F06155211%2Fvillage-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESet%20in%20violence-ridden%20Bastar%2C%20Manoj%20Rupda%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EI%20Named%20My%20Sister%20Silence%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20translated%20by%20Hansda%20Sowvendra%20Shekhar%2C%20is%20an%20elegiac%20narrative%20of%20endemic%20violence%20and%20the%20numbing%20aftermath.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20novel%20is%20an%20embodiment%20of%20Walter%20Benjamin%E2%80%99s%20statement%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%C2%A0document%20of%20civilisation%20that%20is%20not%20at%20the%20same%20time%20a%20document%20of%C2%A0%20barbarism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20200px)%2085vw%2C%20200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11141254%2Fimage-1822-200x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11141254%2Fimage-1822-200x300.png%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11141254%2Fimage-1822.png%20356w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696607%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EI%20Named%20My%20Sister%20Silence%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Manoj%20Rupda%20(Author)%2C%20Hansda%20Sowvendra%20Shekhar%20(Translator).%20(Westland%20Eka%2C%20June%2019%2C%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20eminently%20readable%20170-page%20translation%20brings%20the%20largely%20absent%20perspective%20of%20violence-hit%20Adivasis%20to%20echo%20chambers%20of%20mainstream%20English%20publishing.%20Written%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20a%20tribal%20narrator%2C%20who%20has%20come%20back%20from%20the%20city%20in%20search%20for%20his%20sister%2C%20the%20story%20dwells%20on%20the%20intensely%20familiar%2C%20yet%20an%20emotionally%20distant%20issue%20for%20many%20%E2%80%93%20the%20State%20repression%20of%20tribals%20struggling%20to%20save%20their%20habitat.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20does%20the%20endgame%20of%20growth%20without%20heart%20lead%3B%20who%20benefits%20from%20%E2%80%9Cdevelopment%3B%E2%80%9D%20and%20who%20must%20pay%20its%20price%3F%20In%20how%20many%20ways%3F%20For%20how%20long%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20prologue%20sets%20the%20tone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20hurts%20differently%20to%20watch%20something%20immense%20and%20majestic%20fall%20lifelessly%20to%20its%20knees%20and%20be%20taken%20apart%20by%20powers%20beyond%20its%20control.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20a%20ship%20being%20dismantled%20%E2%80%A6%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20an%20elephant%20being%20eaten%20alive%20by%20wild%20dogs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20a%20forest%20being%20mined%20and%20ravaged%20by%20corporates.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhrases%20like%20%E2%80%9Cfallout%20of%20capitalistic%20neo-imperialism%20in%20a%20globalised%20world%E2%80%9D%20get%20dismantled%2C%20and%20only%20a%20blood-splattered%20green%20silence%20of%20casual%20rape%20and%20encounter%20killings%20reverberates%20in%20the%20reader%E2%80%99s%20mind.%20The%20moral%20decay%20of%20relentless%20oppression%20is%20fleshed%20out%3A%20the%20glint%20of%20metal%20in%20pitch-dark%20jungles%2C%20sandbagged%20barriers%2C%20crumbling%20statues%20of%20%E2%80%98martyrs%2C%E2%80%99%20decrepit%20graves%20of%20comrades%2C%20faded%20red%20flags%2C%20smell%20of%20burnt%20houses.%20Images%20flash%20%E2%80%93%20a%20great%20ship%20splintering%2C%20the%20mute%20eye%20of%20an%20elephant%20being%20torn%20apart%20by%20dogs%2C%20the%20silent%20gaze%20of%20a%20sister%2C%20the%20dead%20eyes%20of%20Adivasis%20%E2%80%93%20outlining%20the%20contours%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Adivasi%20narrator%2C%20who%20had%20left%20the%20forest%20to%20pursue%20studies%2C%20later%20taking%20up%20work%20on%20a%20merchant%20navy%20ship%2C%20comes%20back%20to%20absences.%20The%20sole%20person%20who%20had%20loved%20and%20taken%20care%20of%20him%20when%20he%20was%20little%2C%20his%20stepsister%2C%20has%20joined%20the%20naxals.%20She%20is%20nowhere%20to%20be%20found%2C%20having%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cturned%20herself%20into%20the%20forest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Suspicious%20villagers%20avoid%20him%2C%20telling%20nothing.%20The%20deeper%20he%20goes%20in%2C%20the%20more%20signs%20of%20violence%20he%20encounters%2C%20witnessing%20firsthand%20how%20unequal%20violence%20and%20silence%20about%20it%2C%20scars%20bodies%20and%20psyches.%20Everyone%20%E2%80%93%20his%20school%20mates%2C%20cousins%2C%20neighbours%2C%20women%20and%20girls%20%E2%80%93%20is%20either%20a%20martyr%20and%20a%20patriot%2C%20or%20an%20outlaw%20to%20be%20hunted%20down.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIngeniously%20evil%20schemes%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Flaw-vigilante-powers-impunity%5C%22%3Esalwa%20judum%3C%2Fa%3E%20pit%20brothers%2C%20relatives%2C%20family%20members%20against%20one%20another.%20Coming%20across%20his%20own%20statue%20among%20the%20%E2%80%98martyrs%2C%E2%80%99%20makes%20him%20realise%20that%20%E2%80%9Ct%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20government%20had%20taken%20advantage%20of%20my%20own%20absence%20of%20four%20years%2C%20listed%20me%20as%20an%20SPO%20and%20declared%20me%20as%20having%20been%20killed%20by%20Naxalites.%20They%20had%20also%20perhaps%20embezzled%20the%20compensation%20money%20that%20was%20due%20to%20my%20family%20and%20dependents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20universe%20of%20corporate%20greed%20and%20State%20control%20demands%20ritual%20sacrifice%20of%20the%20Adivasis%E2%80%99%20habitat%20and%20way%20of%20life.%20He%20also%20comes%20face%20to%20face%20with%20his%20evil%20mother%20and%20witnesses%20the%20destitution%20of%20tribals%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98protected%E2%80%99%20camp.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPages%20after%20pages%20would%20be%20written%20about%20warring%20parties%2C%20but%20of%20what%20use%20would%20that%20be%3F%20Who%20would%20write%20about%20the%20people%20who%20had%20been%20ruined%20while%20they%20were%20still%20alive%3F%20Who%20would%20write%20about%20those%20adolescent%20single%20mothers%20who%20bore%20the%20illegitimate%20scions%20of%20men%20from%20the%20paramilitary%20forces%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rootedness%20and%20insularity%20of%20the%20ancient%20forests%20being%20mined%20for%20ore%2C%20contrasts%20with%20his%20ship%20that%E2%80%99s%20constantly%20on%20the%20move%2C%20ferrying%20cheap%20ore%20for%20ever-hungry%20global%20markets.%20After%20a%20brush%20with%20death%20in%20the%20jungle%2C%20the%20narrator%20leaves%20for%20the%20city%20and%20boards%20the%20ship%20again%2C%20only%20to%20find%20that%20market%20failure%20means%20that%20their%20ship%20will%20be%20dismantled%20and%20sold%20as%20scrap.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20people%20and%20their%20forests%20don%E2%80%99t%20count%2C%20nor%20does%20the%20ship%20count%3B%20only%20the%20logic%20of%20the%20market%20counts.%20A%20conversation%20with%20the%20captain%20of%20his%20ship%20leads%20the%20narrator%20to%20understand%20that%20the%20violence%20connecting%20the%20mined%20jungles%2C%20the%20Adivasis%20stripped%20of%20all%20emotion%2C%20and%20the%20ship%20slated%20to%20be%20scrapped%20is%20one%20and%20the%20same.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20violence%20of%20current%20times%20echoes%20the%20dark%20chapters%20of%20genocide%20from%20every%20era%20%E2%80%93%20the%20racist%20lynching%20of%20blacks%20in%20the%20US%2C%20partition%20violence%2C%20and%20the%20manmade%20cycles%20of%20drought%20and%20famine%20in%20Ethiopia%2C%20engendered%20by%20reckless%20eucalypt%20plantations%20catering%20to%20Western%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELiterary%20convictions%20shine%20as%20bright%20as%20political%20ones%20in%20this%20book.%20Without%20saying%20it%20aloud%2C%20the%20realisation%20dawns%20that%20what%20happened%20to%20the%20blacks%20in%20America%20and%20in%20Ethiopia%2C%20and%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20the%20adivasis%2C%20is%20also%20on%20its%20way%20for%20all%20of%20us.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20reading%20the%20original%20and%20the%20translation%2C%20I%20am%20struck%20by%20the%20enhanced%20readability%20achieved%20by%20judicious%20compression%2C%20restructuring%20of%20sentences%2C%20and%20cutting%20out%20repetitions%2C%20while%20staying%20in%20line%20with%20authorial%20intent.%20Both%20sensitivity%20for%20the%20source%20text%2C%20and%20a%20healthy%20respect%20for%20the%20capacities%20and%20possibilities%20of%20the%20English%20language%20are%20on%20display.%20Acting%20as%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20active%20collaborator%2C%20Shekhar%20has%20taken%20several%20aesthetic%20decisions%20that%20yield%20a%20taut%20pace.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChoosing%20%3Cem%3EI%20Named%20My%20Sister%20Silence%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20title%20(instead%20of%20translating%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EKale%20Adhyay%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20the%20translator%20has%20put%20the%20recurring%20motif%20of%20silence%20in%20focus.%20Likewise%2C%20the%20decision%20of%20adding%20a%20brief%20prologue%2C%20and%20of%20giving%20titles%20to%20individual%20chapters%2C%20trains%20attention%20on%20narrative%20themes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20narrator%E2%80%99s%20interior%20monologue%20in%20the%20longish%20first%20chapter%20of%20the%20Hindi%20text%20has%20been%20compressed%20to%20foreground%20portions%20depicting%20the%20ship%E2%80%99s%20imminent%20dismantling%20in%20a%20shipyard.%20This%20tactic%20effectively%20contextualises%20the%20narrator%E2%80%99s%20memories%20about%20the%20ship%2C%20and%20connects%20the%20jungle-focused%20part%20I%20of%20the%20book%20to%20the%20ocean-focused%20part%20II%2C%20imparting%20a%20satisfying%20circularity%20to%20the%20story.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-book-makes-the-call-jerry-pinto-on-the-importance-of-translations-and-experimental-reading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Book%20Makes%20the%20Call%E2%80%99%3A%20Jerry%20Pinto%20on%20the%20Importance%20of%20Translations%20and%20Experimental%20Reading%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdaptations%2C%20cuts%2C%20interpolations%20are%20a%20given%20when%20translating%20drama%2C%20epic%20poetry%2C%20and%20songs.%20However%2C%20deviations%20from%20text%20remain%20a%20vexatious%20issue%20for%20translators%20of%20narrative%20fiction.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20Shekhar%20was%20kind%20enough%20to%20answer%20my%20questions%20on%20considerations%20that%20guided%20his%20translation%20choices.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlease%20share%20why%20you%20chose%20to%20translate%20this%20novel.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20chose%20to%20translate%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKale%20Adhyay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Einto%20English%20for%20two%20reasons.%20First%2C%20I%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20power%20of%20Manoj%20Rupda%E2%80%99s%20writing.%20After%20reading%20and%20thoroughly%20enjoying%20his%20Hindi%20story%2C%20%3Cem%3ETower%20of%20Silence%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20translated%20it.%20I%20became%20a%20fan%20of%20his%20from%20that%20one%20story%20alone.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%2C%20because%20of%20the%20elephant%20scene%20and%20the%20character%20of%20the%20sister%2C%20Madavi%20Irma.%20There%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20third%20reason%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKale%20Adhyay%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20a%20tremendous%20book.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20make%20the%20recurring%20theme%20of%20silence%20the%20focal%20point%20by%20utilising%20it%20for%20the%20title.%20How%20does%20it%20enhance%20the%20fundamental%20meaning%20of%20the%20source%20text%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20overarching%20theme%20of%20the%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EKale%20Adhyay%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ekhamoshi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20silence.%20The%20literal%20translation%20of%20the%20title%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98Dark%20Chapters%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20perhaps%20would%20not%20have%20been%20that%20effective.%20%3Cem%3EI%20Named%20My%20Sister%20Silence%3C%2Fem%3E%20does%20not%20just%20place%20%E2%80%9Ckhamoshi%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Csilence%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20at%20the%20centre%20stage%2C%20it%20also%20gives%20the%20reader%20a%20hint%20of%20what%20they%20can%20expect%20to%20find%20in%20the%20novel.%20Also%2C%20%3Cem%3EI%20Named%20My%20Sister%20Silence%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0sounds%20intriguing%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20it%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhile%20rambling%20sentences%20add%20narrative%20emphasis%20in%20Hindi%2C%20without%20sounding%20odd%2C%20a%20good%20sentence%20in%20English%20needs%20a%20defined%20subject%20and%20is%20often%20structured%20differently.%20Please%20share%20how%20you%20go%20about%20balancing%20the%20essential%20and%20cutting%20the%20superfluous.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20something%20is%20superfluous%2C%20I%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20it%20right%20while%20translating%20the%20text.%20What%20may%20not%20sound%20rambling%20in%20the%20source%20language%2C%20may%20very%20well%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20rambling%20in%20the%20target%20language.%20So%2C%20I%20go%20by%20that%20instinct%20of%20mine%20which%20tells%20me%20that%20I%20should%20keep%20one%20thing%20while%20deleting%20the%20other.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Hindi%20novel%20uses%20words%20like%20%3Cem%3Emaan%2C%20pitaji%2C%20behan%3C%2Fem%3E%20while%20you%20replace%20these%20forms%20of%20address%20with%20%3Cem%3EKako%2C%20Buba%2C%20Yaya.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20certainly%20infuses%20vitality%20and%20makes%20the%20translation%20belong%20to%20its%20milieu.%20How%20did%20this%20come%20about%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EKako%2C%20Buba%2C%20Yaya%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20etc.%20are%20from%20the%20Gondi%20language%20that%20the%20Gond%20people%20(also%20known%20as%20Koitur%20or%20Koya%20people)%20speak.%20I%20needed%20to%20use%20Gondi%20words%20because%20I%20assumed%20that%20the%20people%20living%20in%20a%20village%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20a%20forest%20in%20Bastar%20would%20speak%20their%20mother%20tongue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERozy%20Gawde%2C%20a%20native%20Gondi%20speaker%20based%20in%20Bastar%2C%20from%20the%20Koitur%20community%20gave%20me%20these%20%5Bwords%5D%20and%20I%20cannot%20thank%20her%20enough%20for%20her%20help.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%20that%20the%20author%20in%20you%20is%20taking%20over%20the%20translator%2C%20when%20you%20make%20editorial%20decisions%20on%20the%20efficacy%20of%20the%20translated%20text%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAnswer%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20certainly%20does%2C%20and%20I%20am%20happy%20about%20it.%20Since%20I%20am%20an%20author%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20reader%2C%20first%20and%20foremost%20%E2%80%93%20I%20know%20what%20a%20reader%20might%20expect.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20a%20translator%E2%80%99s%20guilt%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETranslators%20should%20not%20feel%20guilty%20about%20modifying%20the%20translated%20text%20to%20make%20it%20more%20appealing%20and%20concise%2C%20about%20playing%20with%20the%20source%20text%20and%20working%20with%20it%20the%20way%20they%20find%20best.%20Translators%20should%20not%20feel%20guilty%20about%20not%20treating%20the%20source%20text%20with%20reverence%20(which%2C%20most%20of%20the%20time%2C%20is%20just%20an%20undue%20reverence).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20speak%20a%20bit%20on%20the%20considerations%20translators%20should%20keep%20in%20mind%20when%20deviating%20from%20the%20source%20text%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BThere%20is%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20only%20one%20consideration%3A%20Do%20not%20lose%20the%20meaning%20that%20the%20original%2Fsource%20text%20wants%20to%20convey.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBased%20in%20Delhi%2C%20%3Cspan%3EVarsha%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Tiwary%20works%20as%20an%20auditor%2C%20and%20translates%20between%20Hindi%20and%20English.%20She%20also%20writes%20short%20stories%20and%20essays%2C%20which%20have%20appeared%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Bombay%20Literary%20Magazine%3Cem%3E%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707642057000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F06155211%2Fvillage-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-i-named-my-sister-silence-hansda-shekhar-trans