0like%20roads%20and%20bridges.%20Parts%20of%20Delhi%20too%20were%20flooded%20as%20the%20Yamuna%20rose%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fraging-yamuna-nears-all-time-record-level-in-delhi%2Farticleshow%2F101685613.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehighest%20level%20in%2045%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20these%20are%20only%20a%20sample%20of%20stories%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%202023%2C%20heatwaves%20killed%20hundreds%20in%20Mexico%20and%20the%20United%20States%20alone%3B%20heatwaves%20also%20struck%20Europe%2C%20China%2C%20Laos%2C%20and%20Thailand.%20Thousands%20died%20and%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20were%20displaced%20by%20torrential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffloodlist.com%5C%22%3Eflooding%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20wildfires%20in%20dozens%20of%20cities%20across%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Chile%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Haiti%2C%20Spain%2C%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Ivory%20Coast%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Greece%2C%20Libya%E2%80%94to%20name%20a%20few.%20This%20is%20to%20say%20nothing%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F08%2Fclimate-change-food-prices-drought%2F%5C%22%3Eextensive%20damage%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fel-nino-threatens-rice-crops-across-asia%2F7178880.html%5C%22%3Eto%20crops%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20heat%2C%20flood%2C%20fire%2C%20drought%2C%20and%20extreme%20winds%20across%20the%20world.%20As%20has%20frequently%20happened%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2Fng-interactive%2F2023%2Fsep%2F29%2Fthe-hottest-summer-in-human-history-a-visual-timeline%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20again%20declared%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2024%2Fjan%2F09%2F2023-record-world-hottest-climate-fossil-fuel%5C%22%3Ehottest%20year%20ever%20measured%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20globe.%20But%20even%20more%20than%20that%2C%202023%20was%20likely%20the%20hottest%20in%20at%20least%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fweather%2F2023%2F07%2F08%2Fearth-hottest-years-thousands-climate%2F%5C%22%3Ehundred%20and%20twenty-five%20thousand%3C%2Fa%3E%20years.%20Yes%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finsideclimatenews.org%2Fnews%2F11102023%2Fscientists-disagree-about-drivers-of-septembers-temperature-spike%2F%5C%22%3Efar%20beyond%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20we%20consider%20%E2%80%98normal.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20crazy%20as%20the%20weather%20has%20been%2C%20we%20are%20sure%20to%20see%20worse%20in%20the%20years%20ahead.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.ametsoc.org%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fclim%2F35%2F3%2FJCLI-D-21-0200.1.xml%5C%22%3Efrequency%2C%20extent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20intensity%20of%20such%20severe%20weather%20is%20increasing%20due%20to%20global%20warming%20caused%20by%20the%20accumulation%20of%20excess%20greenhouse%20gasses%20(GHGs)%20%E2%80%93%20like%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20%E2%80%93%20that%20trap%20heat%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20These%20excess%20GHGs%20result%20directly%20from%20industrial%20and%20other%20economic%20activities%20linked%20to%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20destroying%20forests%20and%20wetlands.%20The%20excess%20heat%20they%20trap%20is%20causing%20the%20ice%20to%20rapidly%20melt%20away%20from%20the%20Arctic%20Ocean%20and%20Greenland%2C%20exposing%20dark%20waters%20and%20rock%20surfaces%20that%20directly%20absorb%20even%20more%20solar%20radiation%3B%20this%20then%20drives%20its%20own%20contribution%20to%20further%20warming%20%E2%80%93%20and%20thus%20further%20melting%20%E2%80%93%20in%20what%E2%80%99s%20called%20an%20%3Cem%3Eamplifying%20feedback%20loop%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20of%20several%20in%20the%20climate%20system.%20Over%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%20the%20lists%20of%20nations%20and%20cities%20hit%20by%20floods%20will%20grow%20longer%2C%20the%20heatwave%20death%20tolls%20more%20harrowing%2C%20the%20crop%20losses%20much%20higher.%20This%20much%20we%20already%20know%20will%20happen%2C%20as%20the%20globe%20continues%20to%20warm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11114734%2FS1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221119%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11114734%2FS1.jpg%201119w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11114734%2FS1-300x98.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11114734%2FS1-1024x336.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696588%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22367%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20scientists%2C%20environmentalists%2C%20and%20politicians%20have%20understood%20for%20decades%20that%20warming%20the%20world%20by%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20would%20result%20in%20these%20kinds%20of%20catastrophes.%20For%20decades%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20been%20holding%20scientific%20and%20policy%20talks%20to%20address%20the%20problem.%20The%20leading%20group%20of%20talkers%20is%20called%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20(IPCC)%2C%20convened%20by%20the%20United%20Nations.%20Their%20twenty-eighth%20annual%20meeting%20%E2%80%93%20or%20COP28%20%E2%80%93%20was%20hosted%20by%20Dubai%20in%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20310px)%2085vw%2C%20310px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22310%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22426%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20few%20years%2C%20the%20IPCC%20publishes%20major%20technical%20reports%20detailing%20the%20state%20of%20global%20GHG%20emissions%2C%20with%20a%20strong%20focus%20on%20carbon-dioxide%2C%20describing%20how%20this%20might%20affect%20the%20climate%2C%20different%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20civilisational%20infrastructures%20now%20and%20in%20the%20future.%20They%20outline%20a%20range%20of%20theoretical%20scenarios%20to%20guide%20governments%20and%20other%20institutions%20as%20they%20set%20targets%20to%20reduce%20fossil%20fuel%20burning%2C%20forest%20and%20wetland%20degradation%2C%20and%20other%20activities%20that%20directly%20contribute%20to%20the%20accumulation%20of%20atmospheric%20GHGs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Fsite%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2022%2F06%2FSPM_version_report_LR.pdf%5C%22%3EThey%E2%80%99ve%20determined%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20the%20average%20global%20temperature%20is%20likely%20to%20rise%20by%201.5%C2%BAC%20between%202030%E2%80%932053%2C%20relative%20to%20what%20it%20was%20before%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20threshold%20nearly%20touched%20already%20in%202023%2C%20when%20the%20globe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwmo.int%2Fmedia%2Fnews%2Fwmo-confirms-2023-smashes-global-temperature-record%5C%22%3Ewarmed%20by%201.45%C2%BAC%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20quantifying%20and%20describing%20the%20extreme%20threats%20that%20lie%20beyond%20this%20temperature%20threshold.%20These%20findings%20have%20put%20pressure%20on%20governments%20to%20make%20pledges%20about%20lowering%20carbon%20dioxide%20emissions%20within%20their%20borders.%20Perhaps%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20triumph%20is%20in%20helping%20to%20shift%20the%20global%20conversation%20on%20climate%20justice%20and%20equitability%2C%20finally%20establishing%20the%20need%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98loss%20and%20damage%20fund%2C%E2%80%99%20whereby%20wealthier%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20who%20have%20historically%20contributed%20the%20far%20greater%20share%20of%20GHGs%20already%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20%E2%80%93%20can%20help%20poorer%20nations%20adapt%20to%20climate%20change%20and%20deal%20with%20its%20mounting%20onslaughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IPCC%20reports%20are%20meticulous%2C%20exhaustive%2C%20based%20on%20top-notch%20science%2C%20and%20essential%20to%20our%20understanding%20of%20how%20the%20climate%20and%20Earth-system%20work.%20Running%20into%20thousands%20of%20pages%2C%20the%20reports%20are%20valiantly%20written%2C%20compiled%20by%20teams%20of%20earnest%20scientists%20and%20subject%20matter%20experts%20across%20a%20range%20of%20disciplines%20from%20around%20the%20globe.%20Yet%20despite%20this%20tremendous%20effort%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwedocs.unep.org%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F20.500.11822%2F40932%2FEGR2022_ESEN.pdf%3Fsequence%3D8%5C%22%3Egovernments%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fnews-and-stories%2Fpress-release%2Fnations-must-go-further-current-paris-pledges-or-face-global-warming%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNairobi%2C%2525252020%25252520November%252525202023%25252520%252525E2%25252580%25252593%25252520As%2Cpre-industrial%25252520levels%25252520this%25252520century%2C%5C%22%3Ewavering%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20emissions%20reduction%20commitments%20and%20reneging%20on%20their%20contributions%20to%20the%20loss%20and%20damage%20fund.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20world%20is%20screaming%20right%20past%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20recommended%20warming%20threshold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%20during%20the%20nearly%20three%20decades%20that%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20heroic%20work%20has%20been%20ongoing%2C%20GHG%20emissions%20have%20on